# Cross-platform line ending normalization
# ==========================================
# 確保 repo 內一律 LF，checkout 時依平台自動處理。
# 對 FUSE 掛載環境尤其重要 — 避免 CRLF/LF 混用造成的 diff 雜訊。

* text=auto eol=lf

# Source code
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.py    text eol=lf
*.go    text eol=lf
*.js    text eol=lf
*.jsx   text eol=lf
*.ts    text eol=lf
*.html  text eol=lf
*.css   text eol=lf

# Config / Data
*.yaml  text eol=lf
*.yml   text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
*.toml  text eol=lf

# Documentation
*.md    text eol=lf
*.txt   text eol=lf

# Dockerfile / Makefile
Dockerfile* text eol=lf
Makefile    text eol=lf

# Windows-specific shells — MUST be CRLF.
# cmd.exe mis-parses LF-only .bat files (treats every word as a command,
# reports "'REM' is not recognized" etc.); PowerShell is tolerant of LF
# but convention is CRLF. Without these overrides, `* text=auto eol=lf`
# above silently strips CR on every git operation (stash/pop, checkout,
# pull), breaking wrappers in scripts/ops/ for Windows MCP sessions.
# See docs/internal/windows-mcp-playbook.md LL #55 + #56.
*.bat   text eol=crlf
*.cmd   text eol=crlf
*.ps1   text eol=crlf

# Binary — 不做任何轉換
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.ico   binary
*.gz    binary
*.tar   binary
*.zip   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary

# Git LFS — visual regression baselines
# ====================================
# Playwright `toHaveScreenshot()` stores per-spec baselines under
# `tests/e2e/<spec>-snapshots/`. Routing these PNGs through Git LFS keeps
# the main pack lean even as baselines accumulate over time. Refines the
# 2026-05-05 VR strategy decision (commit-to-git via Playwright built-in)
# by activating the documented LFS escape route earlier than the original
# >30-snapshots threshold — chosen to avoid lock-in to bloated history
# now that VR is going live.
#
# `-text` overrides the earlier `* text=auto eol=lf` default so LFS sees
# raw bytes (no line-ending normalization on what's logically opaque blobs).
tests/e2e/*-snapshots/*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
